      "message": "Note that this is insufficient, see \u0027-help\u0027 output.\n\nBy default luci/server binaries start in \"development\" mode optimized for local hacking. When running for real they need to start in production mode (enabled by \u0027-prod\u0027) flag. It will *require* few other flags that are necessary for correct work of LUCI stack. See qscheduler for example: https://chrome-internal.googlesource.com/infra/infra_internal/+/refs/heads/master/services/deployments/qscheduler-dev/manifests/deployments.yaml#26\n\nIn particular you\u0027ll need -root-secret-path if you going to use XSRF token or any other tokens generated via go.chromium.org/luci/server/tokens library.",
